text: the application is severely lacking in ux in a couple key area most frustrating to me is the list of song why the hell is the menu button and scroll bar so close together most of the time i try to very precisely click a song is menu button and instead the application interprets the application a pressing the scroll bar causing the application to scroll to some completely unrelated part of the song list i listen to some longer audio like hour long and trying to move forward or backward a few second is nearly impossible with the scroll bar and there are no button option like skip back second the search feature doe not search your local catalog just music on the internet it would be way more helpful if that search feature worked on music that is already on the device and in the goole play music library the final straw was today when i updated the android operating system after the update goole play music no longer is able to read from my sd card after trying many remedy nothing has worked the sd card is definitely there and the file are definitely there i can view the file through the file viewer on the phone
original_text: The app is severely lacking in UX in a couple key areas.  - Most frustrating to me is the list of songs: why the hell is the menu button and scroll bar so close together? Most of the time I try to very precisely click a song's menu button and instead the app interprets it as pressing the scroll bar, causing the app to scroll to some completely unrelated part of the songs list. - I listen to some longer audio (like hours long) and trying to move forward or backward a few seconds is nearly impossible with the scroll bar and there are no button options like "skip back 10 seconds". - The search feature doesn't search your local catalog, just music on the internet: it would be way more helpful if that search feature worked on music that's already on the device and in the Google Play Music library.  The final straw was today when I updated the Android operating system. After the update Google Play Music no longer is able to read from my SD card; after trying many remedies nothing has worked. The SD card is definitely there and the files are definitely there (I can view them through the file viewer on the phone).
